<header class="labs-header">
  <div class="labs-eyebrow">site tree — variants on baseline</div>
  <p class="labs-lede">
    Same geometry, same topology. Each variant tweaks one axis so we can isolate what pulls the page toward "designed" vs "handmade".
  </p>
</header>

<div class="labs-grid">

  <div class="lab-card lab-card-baseline">
    <p class="lab-axis">baseline</p>
    <div class="lab-card-title">
      <a href="/site-tree/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Site tree (production)</a>
      <span class="lab-card-route">/site-tree/</span>
    </div>
    <p class="lab-card-note">
      Filled trapezoid trunk + filled tapered branches. OKLCH palette. Source Serif italic labels + IBM Plex Mono small-caps subs. Animated dashed river. "you are here" koan.
    </p>
    <iframe class="lab-card-frame" src="/site-tree/" title="baseline site tree"></iframe>
  </div>

  <div class="lab-card">
    <p class="lab-axis">axis — fill vs stroke</p>
    <div class="lab-card-title">
      <a href="/site-tree-v1/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">V1 — outlined</a>
      <span class="lab-card-route">/site-tree-v1/</span>
    </div>
    <p class="lab-card-note">
      Trunk and branches become <em>stroked outlines</em>, not filled solids. Everything else unchanged. Reads less "designed weight", more "diagram." Loses some presence; gains airiness.
    </p>
    <iframe class="lab-card-frame" src="/site-tree-v1/" title="outlined variant"></iframe>
  </div>

  <div class="lab-card">
    <p class="lab-axis">axis — geometry</p>
    <div class="lab-card-title">
      <a href="/site-tree-v2/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">V2 — curved &amp; uneven</a>
      <span class="lab-card-route">/site-tree-v2/</span>
    </div>
    <p class="lab-card-note">
      Trunk edges bow into a subtle S-curve. Branches use beziers instead of straight tapers. Writing node sits ~14px lower than Consulting (uneven canopy heights). About line and river get a slight arc. The geometric symmetry breaks <em>just</em> enough.
    </p>
    <iframe class="lab-card-frame" src="/site-tree-v2/" title="curved variant"></iframe>
  </div>

  <div class="lab-card">
    <p class="lab-axis">axis — texture</p>
    <div class="lab-card-title">
      <a href="/site-tree-v3/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">V3 — textured</a>
      <span class="lab-card-route">/site-tree-v3/</span>
    </div>
    <p class="lab-card-note">
      Same baseline geometry but every shape passes through an <code>feTurbulence</code> displacement filter — paths jitter as if drawn by hand at low amplitude (scale 1.4, baseFrequency 0.018). Subtle; survives at a glance.
    </p>
    <iframe class="lab-card-frame" src="/site-tree-v3/" title="textured variant"></iframe>
  </div>

  <div class="lab-card">
    <p class="lab-axis">axis — typography &amp; ground</p>
    <div class="lab-card-title">
      <a href="/site-tree-v4/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">V4 — warm paper</a>
      <span class="lab-card-route">/site-tree-v4/</span>
    </div>
    <p class="lab-card-note">
      Stage gets a parchment-warm background tint. Labels swap to EB Garamond <em>upright</em> (not italic). IBM Plex Mono sub-labels dropped. Koan dropped. Pulls the page from "design system surface" toward "page from a book". Most aggressive variant.
    </p>
    <iframe class="lab-card-frame" src="/site-tree-v4/" title="warm paper variant"></iframe>
  </div>

  <div class="lab-card" style="background: color-mix(in srgb, oklch(96% 0.04 80) 35%, var(--bg));">
    <p class="lab-axis">composed — V4 + V2 + tremor</p>
    <div class="lab-card-title">
      <a href="/site-tree-v5/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">V5 — after Alexander</a>
      <span class="lab-card-route">/site-tree-v5/</span>
    </div>
    <p class="lab-card-note">
      V4's parchment ground + upright EB Garamond, composed with V2's curved trunk and uneven branches. Low-amplitude tremor filter applied to tree shapes only. A faint soil horizon anchors the tree in ground, breaking before the river. Local symmetries, no global symmetry. The "page from <em>A Pattern Language</em>" variant.
    </p>
    <iframe class="lab-card-frame" src="/site-tree-v5/" title="alexander variant"></iframe>
  </div>

</div>
